Eric Ikhilae, Abuja Governors under the auspices of the Nigeria Governors Forum (NGF) are currently meeting in Abuja to harmonise their positions on some issues of national importance. The meeting currently on-going at the Transcorp Hilton hotel, has most of the governors, including Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State, who just walked in a moment ago, in attendance. The meetings’ agenda includes “udidate on Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation PHC Meeting in Seattle, November 12-13, 2019 and other side meetings. “Update on deductions for budget support facility “Proposal for recovery of funds due to State Governments (Withholding Tax (WHT), Collection of Ground Rent. NTEL, MTEL etc.) “Briefing by NEC Ad-hoc Committee on Excess Crude and other Special Accounts of the Federation H.E. Governor Nasir El-Rufai. “Update on the Primary Health Care Under One Roof (PHCOUR) and other health related matters.” Details shortly.